			Technical Security
		</h3>
		<h4>
			Children
		</h4>
		<p>
			The Web site is not directed to individuals under eighteen years of age, and <%= APPLICATION_NAME %> does not intend to collect any personally-identifiable information from such individuals.
		</p>
		<h4>
			Cookies
		</h4>
		<p>
			Cookies are electronic files on your hard drive. Cookies cannot read data off your hard drive; they store identification information about you. <%= APPLICATION_NAME %>, like the operators of many other Web sites, uses the cookies to identify you when you visit the Web site. <%= APPLICATION_NAME %> may also use the cookie to recognize you to help ensure the security of confidential information. <%= APPLICATION_NAME %> uses the information from cookies to personalize services and determine the amount and type of traffic at the Web site. Cookies also provide us with information about your clickstream, that is, the way that you navigate through the Web site, so that we can better design the Web site for your use. Most browsers allow you to disable or delete your cookies. <%= APPLICATION_NAME %> would prefer to provide you with personalized services through cookies and not all services may be available to those who disable or delete cookies. 
